item.description:
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;These .5 GPH drippers are in-line drippers that drip in the center so they can be added together using 1/4-in vinyl tubing to make a line of drip.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;A 25 PSI pressure regulator (&lt;span style=&quot;color: #3366ff;&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://misterlandscaper.com/25-psi-pressure-regulator-drippers&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: #3366ff;&quot;&gt;MLD-25PR&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;) and a faucet filter (&lt;span style=&quot;color: #3366ff;&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://misterlandscaper.com/150-mesh-faucet-filter-for-micro-sprays-drippers-2&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: #3366ff;&quot;&gt;MLFF-41&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;) are &lt;span style=&quot;color: #ff0000;&quot;&gt;highly recommended&lt;/span&gt; to be used first at the water source when using these .5 GPH drippers&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;The Drippers connect with 1/4-in Vinyl to create a line of Drip. Place the drippers wherever they are needed on the line.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Use these .5 GPH add-a-drippers to slowly and gently water window boxes of flowers, rows of vegetables, potted plants and ring around trees.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;If you are using the 1/4-in In-Line Drip Tubing (&lt;span style=&quot;color: #3366ff;&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://misterlandscaper.com/100-ft-coil-14-in-in-line-drip-tubing&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: #3366ff;&quot;&gt;MLD-QDT100&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;) and more water is needed on certain plants, you can add these Add-A-Drippers. If a dripper becomes clogged, you can cut the dripper out of the MLD-QDT-100 and replace it with one of the MLD-AAD.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;When installing, you can run up to 30-ft of 1/4-in Vinyl from the 1/2-in Poly Tube and install up to 30 drippers in a single line.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Use the enclosed 1/4-in coupler to attach the 1/4-in vinyl to the 1/2-in poly tubing&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Push the red barb of the dripper into the end of the 1/4-in vinyl &lt;span style=&quot;color: #993300;&quot;&gt;(we recommend installing the red side facing the water pressure)&lt;/span&gt; then attach to other end of the vinyl onto the black barb of the dripper.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Repeat this last step until you have up to 30 of these drippers installed 1/4-in off a single 30-ft line of 1/4-in vinyl from the 1/2-in poly tubing.&#160;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;After the last dripper is installed, put a short 2-in piece of vinyl on the black barb end of the dripper and then push in the enclosed goof plug to end the 1/4-in line.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 12pt; background-color: #ff0000;&quot;&gt;Before installing the goof plug, turn on the water and allow a flow of water to clean out any debris that may have entered the line during installation.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Our 1/4-in support stakes (&lt;span style=&quot;color: #3366ff;&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://misterlandscaper.com/14-in-vinyl-support-stake-qty-10&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: #3366ff;&quot;&gt;MLT-DST&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;) can be used to securely hold the 1/4-in vinyl along the row of plants.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Also use our 1/4-in tees and elbows (&lt;span style=&quot;color: #3366ff;&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://misterlandscaper.com/14-in-combo-pack-teeselbowscouplers-qty-4-each&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: #3366ff;&quot;&gt;MLT-ATE&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;) to run the 1/4-in vinyl in opposing directions or in tight corners to supply water to these drippers.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;(5 Drippers / 1 Coupler / 1 Goof Plug Per Bag)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: #ff0000; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Drippers and Drip Tubing should NEVER be buried&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt; &#160;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;When installing any irrigation system it is important to be aware of manufacturer recommendations and potential system limitations. Please be aware of the following:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&#160;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;RECOMMENDATIONS&#160;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&#160;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;We recommend using our 25 PSI Pressure Regulator (&lt;span style=&quot;color: #3366ff;&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://misterlandscaper.com/25-psi-pressure-regulator-drippers&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: #3366ff;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: #3366ff;&quot;&gt;MLD-25PR&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;) with any drip system.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;We also recommend using our faucet filter (&lt;span style=&quot;color: #3366ff;&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://misterlandscaper.com/150-mesh-faucet-filter-for-micro-sprays-drippers-2&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: #3366ff;&quot;&gt;MLFF-41&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;) with any drip system.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Drippers and Drip Tubing should NEVER be buried.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&#160;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;MAXIMUM RUNS&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&#160;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;1/4-in Vinyl Tubing&lt;/strong&gt; - When installing, you can run up to 30-ft of 1/4-in Vinyl from the 1/2-in Poly and install up to 30 Drippers in a single line.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;1/2-in Poly Tubing&lt;/strong&gt; - Run up to 300-ft of our 1/2-in Poly Tubing and connect up to 13 individual 30-ft runs of our 1/4-in Vinyl Tubing, installing up to 30 of our .5 gph Add-A-Drippers per individual run.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&#160;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Maximum operating pressure for Drippers: &#160;25 PSI&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Minimum opersting water pressure for Drippers: &#160;5 PSI&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;These .5 GPH drippers are pressure compensated to keep a constant drip/flow of .5 GPH at various water pressures up to 25 PSI.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;A 25 PSI pressure regulator (&lt;span style=&quot;color: #3366ff;&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;/drip-irrigation-25-psi-pressure-regulator-for-dripper-systems&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: #3366ff;&quot;&gt;MLD-25PR&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;) and a faucet filter (&lt;span style=&quot;color: #3366ff;&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;/drip-irrigation-micro-spray-50-mesh-in-line-filter-with-three-quarter-inch-hose-threads&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: #3366ff;&quot;&gt;MLFF-41&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;) are &lt;span style=&quot;color: #ff0000;&quot;&gt;highly recommended&lt;/span&gt; to be used first at the water source when using these .5 GPH drippers. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Use this dripper to slowly water a potted plant or landscapes using only .5 GPH of water. They are ergonomically designed with a wide-winged top to make the installation easier.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;The water supply enters into the dripper from the red barbed end, and then the water is dispersed from the black stem end.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Install these drippers directly into the 1/2-in poly tubing by first snapping a hole using either of our punch tools (&lt;span style=&quot;color: #3366ff;&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;/drip-irrigation-micro-spray-hole-punch-tool-and-eight-goof-plugs&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: #3366ff;&quot;&gt;MLA-51&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; or &lt;span style=&quot;color: #3366ff;&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;/drip-irrigation-micro-spray-all-in-one-tool-makes-installation-easier&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: #3366ff;&quot;&gt;MLA-TOOL&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;). Use our goof plugs if you snap a hole in the wrong place or want to relocate the dripper.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;These drippers can also be installed by running a piece of 1/4-in vinyl tubing to the plant from the 1/2-in poly tubing using the enclosed 1/4-in barbed couplers, then pushing in the dripper at the other end of the 1/4-in vinyl next to the plant.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: #ff0000;&quot;&gt;Before installing the last dripper, turn on the water to allow a flow of water to clean out any debris that may have entered the line during installation.&lt;/span&gt;&#160;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Our 1/4-in support stakes (&lt;span style=&quot;color: #3366ff;&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;/drip-irrigation-micro-spray-one-quarter-inch-support-stakes-for-vinyl-and-drip-tubing&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: #3366ff;&quot;&gt;MLT-DST&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;) can be used to securely hold the 1/4-in vinyl tubing and .5 GPH dripper near the plant.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Also use our 1/4-in tees and elbows (&lt;span style=&quot;color: #3366ff;&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;/drip-irrigation-micro-spray-one-quarter-inch-vinyl-tubing-connectors-tees-elbows&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: #3366ff;&quot;&gt;MLT-ATE&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;) to run the 1/4-in vinyl tubing in opposing directions or in tight corners to supply water to these drippers.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
