&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;1/4-in Vinyl Tubing&lt;/strong&gt; - Run up to 100-ft of our 1/4-in Vinyl Tubing, installing up to 20 of these .5 GPH PC drippers&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;1/2-in Poly Tubing&lt;/strong&gt; - Run&#160;up to 500-ft of our 1/2-in Poly Tubing, installing up to 500 of these .5 GPH PC drippers&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;You can add drippers to your Micro&#160;Spray System: run up to 300-ft of our 1/2-in Poly Tubing installing&#160;up to 30 of the Micro Spray Assemblies (&lt;a href=&quot;/drip-irrigation-micro-spray-green-landscape-stake-assembly&quot;&gt;MLS-211&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;/drip-irrigation-micro-spray-black-landscape-stake-assembly&quot;&gt;MLS-BLA&lt;/a&gt;&#160;or &lt;a href=&quot;/micro-spray-tan-landscape-stake-assembly&quot;&gt;MLS-TAN&lt;/a&gt;) &amp; less than 10 Drippers off one faucet using a 25 PSI Pressure Regulator (&lt;a href=&quot;/drip-irrigation-25-psi-pressure-regulator-for-dripper-systems&quot;&gt;MLD-25PR&lt;/a&gt;).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;When incorporating pressure compensating drippers, the maximum number of micro sprays will be reduced. The more drippers added, the lower the maximum recommended Stake Assemblies or Mister Risers. As an easy guide, each Stake Assembly or Mister Riser is equal to (20) twenty .5 GPH Pressure Compensation Drippers. Use this formula when determining how many Stake Assemblies or Mister Risers to remove.&lt;/span&gt;
