&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;You can add drippers to your Micro&#160;Spray System: run up to 300-ft of our 1/2-in Poly Tubing installing&#160;up to 30 of the Micro Spray Assemblies (&lt;span style=&quot;color: #3366ff;&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;/drip-irrigation-micro-spray-green-landscape-stake-assembly&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: #3366ff;&quot;&gt;MLS-211&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;,&#160;&lt;a href=&quot;/drip-irrigation-micro-spray-black-landscape-stake-assembly&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: #3366ff;&quot;&gt;MLS-BLA&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&#160;or&#160;&lt;a href=&quot;/micro-spray-tan-landscape-stake-assembly&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: #3366ff;&quot;&gt;MLS-TAN&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;) &amp; less than 10 Drippers off one faucet using a 25 PSI Pressure Regulator (&lt;span style=&quot;color: #3366ff;&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;/drip-irrigation-25-psi-pressure-regulator-for-dripper-systems&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: #3366ff;&quot;&gt;MLD-25PR&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;When incorporating pressure compensating drippers, the maximum number of micro sprays will be reduced. The more drippers added, the lower the maximum recommended&#160;Stake Assemblies or Mister Risers. As an easy guide, each Stake Assembly or Mister Riser is equal to (10) ten 1 GPH Pressure Compensation Drippers. Use this formula when determining how many Stake Assemblies or Mister Risers to remove.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&#160;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maximum operating pressure for Drippers: &#160;25 PSI&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Minimum opersting water pressure for Drippers: &#160;5 PSI&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

