&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;These 2 GPH drippers are pressure-compensated to keep a constant drip/flow of 2 GPH at various water pressures up to 25 PSI.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;A 25 PSI pressure regulator (&lt;a href=&quot;/drip-irrigation-25-psi-pressure-regulator-for-dripper-systems&quot;&gt;MLD-25PR&lt;/a&gt;) and a faucet filter (&lt;a href=&quot;/drip-irrigation-micro-spray-50-mesh-in-line-filter-with-three-quarter-inch-hose-threads&quot;&gt;MLFF-41&lt;/a&gt;) are highly recommended to be used first at the water source when using these 2 GPH drippers. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Use this dripper to slowly water a potted plant or landscapes using only 2 GPH of water. They are ergonomically designed with a wide-winged top to make the installation easier.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;The water supply enters into the dripper from the green barbed end, and the water is dispersed from the black stem end. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Install these drippers directly into the 1/2-in poly tubing by first snapping a hole using either of our punch tools (&lt;a href=&quot;/drip-irrigation-micro-spray-hole-punch-tool-and-eight-goof-plugs&quot;&gt;MLA-51&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=&quot;/drip-irrigation-micro-spray-all-in-one-tool-makes-installation-easier&quot;&gt;MLA-TOOL&lt;/a&gt;). Use our goof plug if you snap a hole in the wrong place or want to relocate the dripper.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;These drippers can also be installed by running a piece of 1/4-in vinyl tubing to the plant from the 1/2-in poly tubing using the 1/4-in barbed couplers (&lt;a href=&quot;/drip-irrigation-micro-spray-one-quarter-inch-barb-and-barb-couplers&quot;&gt;MLT-BXB&lt;/a&gt;), then pushing in the dripper at the other end of the 1/4-in vinyl next to the plant.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: #ff0000; font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Before installing the last dripper, turn on the water to allow a flow of water to clean out any debris that may have entered the line during installation.&#160;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Our 1/4-in support stakes (&lt;a href=&quot;/drip-irrigation-micro-spray-one-quarter-inch-support-stakes-for-vinyl-and-drip-tubing&quot;&gt;MLT-DST&lt;/a&gt;) can be used to securely hold the 1/4-in vinyl tubing and 2 GPH dripper near the plant.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Also use our 1/4-in tees and elbows (&lt;a href=&quot;/drip-irrigation-micro-spray-one-quarter-inch-vinyl-tubing-connectors-tees-elbows&quot;&gt;MLT-ATE)&lt;/a&gt; to run the 1/4-in vinyl tubing in opposing directions or in tight corners to supply water to these drippers.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
