&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;Starting with the Stake: The high-quality resins used in the mold make the stake nearly indestructible in the field.&#160;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;The 1/4-in Vinyl Tubing is some of the most flexible in the industry. This tubing is also made with UV blocking resins, which make it highly resistant to deterioration over time.&#160;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;The assembly&#39;s flow control features start with a 10 GPH Violet Flow Controller. This flow control is responsible for allowing the use of up to 50 Stake Assemblies on a single 300 foot line of 1/2-in Poly Tubing (This is based on a household water pressure of 40-50 PSI).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;The next control feature is the On/Off Valve. As it sounds, this valve allows individual stakes to be turned on and off. But it also works to increase and decrease the size of individual spray patterns.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;Finally, each stake assembly comes with a vinyl collar. Though small, the vinyl collar is an important part of the system. When threading misters into the vinyl tubing, the collar must be in place to prevent the mister from blowing out under high pressures.&#160;&lt;br /&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;The Landscape Stake Assembly is a staple in most Mister Landscaper micro sprinkler systems. It is simple to install, with easy controls, and offers the most flexibility right where the watering happens.&#160;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
