&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;RECOMMENDATIONS &amp; LIMITATIONS&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;When installing any irrigation system it is important to be aware of manufacturer recommendations and potential system limitations. Please be aware of the following:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;margin: 0px; min-height: 14px; font-family: Helvetica;&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;The Electronic Mister Timer must always be the first thing attached to the faucet in any Mister Landscaper system. Regulators, Filters, Backflow Prevention Valves, and any other adapters will always be installed after the timer.&#160;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;margin: 0px; font-family: Helvetica;&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;When winterizing your system, before the first frost (This includes the Southern Region) completely remove the Electronic Mister Timer, remove the batteries and store inside.&#160;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;margin: 0px; font-family: Helvetica;&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;Minimum water pressure to open the timer valve is 20 PSI. Maximum water pressure should not exceed 80 PSI.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;margin: 0px; font-family: Helvetica;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;Rechargable batteries are not recommended.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin: 0px; min-height: 14px; font-family: Helvetica;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&#160;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin: 0px; min-height: 14px; font-family: Helvetica;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&#160;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin: 0px; min-height: 14px; font-family: Helvetica;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;For &lt;strong&gt;Technical Support&lt;/strong&gt; call 877-283-0697 Ext. 129 or email &lt;a href=&quot;mailto:misterlandscaper@melnor.com&quot;&gt;misterlandscaper@melnor.com&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;margin: 0px; min-height: 14px; font-family: Helvetica;&quot;&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;img src=&quot;/Content/Images/uploaded/Timer - Prop65 Warning.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;389&quot; height=&quot;62&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;S to &#160;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul style=&quot;list-style-type: disc;&quot;&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Connects directly to any outdoor faucet.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Adjustable Dripper Stakes have a rotating top that allow the flow of water to be adjusted from a 1 GPH drip up to a small (2.5-ft diameter spray pattern) 10 GPH, 360&#186;, 8-stream spray.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Each Dripper Stake comes with a removable 1/4-in Coupler to be used when connecting to lines of 1/2-in Poly Tubing. (simply break off coupler from side of stake)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;By tightening the top, Dripper Stakes can be shut off completely for added control.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;In under thirty minutes you can have this kit installed, watering up to 8 potted plants.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;To complete your system, simply run a piece of the 1/4-in Vinyl Tubing from the last 1/4-in Tee fitting to the last Dripper Stake/Pot.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;RECOMMENDATIONS &amp; LIMITATIONS&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;When installing any irrigation system it is important to be aware of manufacturer recommendations and potential system limitations. Please be aware of the following:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul style=&quot;list-style-type: disc;&quot;&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;We recommend using our 25 PSI Pressure Regulator (&lt;a href=&quot;/drip-irrigation-25-psi-pressure-regulator-for-dripper-systems&quot;&gt;MLD-25PR&lt;/a&gt;) with any drip system&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;We also recommend using our faucet filter (&lt;a href=&quot;/drip-irrigation-micro-spray-50-mesh-in-line-filter-with-three-quarter-inch-hose-threads&quot;&gt;MLFF-41&lt;/a&gt;) with any drip system&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Due to limited water flow through 1/4-in Vinyl Tubing, no more than one kit (8 Dripper Stakes) can be installed on a faucet&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Due to limited water flow through 1/4-in Vinyl Tubing, no more than three Dripper Stakes in a daisy-chained group will deliver full 10 GPH output. All other installed stakes will function at less than 10 GPH, even if they are turned on completely&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;To run up to four kits (32 Dripper Stakes) from a single outdoor faucet, 1/2-in Poly Tubing must first be installed as the main line.&#160;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;When increasing the water output, be sure not to over rotate the top, as it can come off and become lost.&#160;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: #ff0000;&quot;&gt;Drippers and Drip Tubing should NEVER be buried.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

